.TH "ps3_vuart_irq_setup" 9 "ps3_vuart_irq_setup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ps3_vuart_irq_setup \- Setup the system virtual uart virq.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ps3_vuart_irq_setup
.BI "(enum ps3_cpu_binding cpu "  ","
.BI "void* virt_addr_bmp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *virq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
enum ps3_cpu_binding indicating the cpu the interrupt should be
serviced on.
.IP "virt_addr_bmp" 12
The caller supplied virtual uart interrupt bitmap.
.IP "virq" 12
The assigned Linux virq.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The system supports only a single virtual uart, so multiple calls without
freeing the interrupt will return a wrong state error.
